&lt;p&gt;Dreaming of a New Challenge? &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Hywel Dda University Health Board has the role for you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for the post of Consultant Anaesthetist at Bronglais General Hospital in Aberystwyth. The hospital is part of Hywel Dda University Health Board.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hywel Dda University Health Board is one of seven NHS Health Boards in Wales serving a population of circa 389,000 with over 9,500 staff. It is an integrated health body, ensuring the delivery of high quality primary, community, mental health and secondary care services, and it is responsible for the health and wellbeing of people across Carmarthenshire, Ceredigion and Pembrokeshire. It also provides a range of services for people living in south Gwynedd and Powys. Integrated health boards are a key first step in creating a world class NHS in Wales. Primary care and community services are delivered through: 55 GP practices, 51 Dental practices, 100 Community pharmacies, 52 Optometry premises, 8 Community hospitals, 11 Health centres.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Health Board has an excellent reputation for the provision of quality services, which are highly valued by local people.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A successful candidate will join a team of nine consultants and one associate specialist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All members of the department work fully flexible rotas providing very good work life balance. As our department does not host any trainee doctors the role of a Consultant includes both first and second on-call, as well as elective work. On calls cover emergency Anaesthesia, Obstetrics and Intensive Care. Please note that the first on call Anaesthetist is required to stay at the hospital as a resident also at night. Elective work will include day time ITU cover, and Anaesthesia for General Surgery, Urology, Orthopaedic, Gynaecology, Obstetric, and Ophthalmic surgery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should hold fellowship of the Royal College of Anaesthetists or equivalent and be eligible for inclusion in the Specialist Register.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable, but not essential. Aberystwyth is the principle town in the county of Ceredigion. The town is situated in a picturesque spot in West Wales and is one of the most beautiful and attractive in the country.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are invited to visit us to explore this exciting opportunity. International candidates are welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact Dr Jack Zeber, Consultant Anaesthetist for further information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please ensure that you read the person specification carefully and that you meet all the essential criteria prior to applying. We encourage and welcome pre-interview visits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Jacek Zeber - Consultant Anaesthetist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;jacek.zeber@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
